  "texts": [
    "In an SAI system, AI benefits from a continuous stream of new user-provided data to refine itself, while humans benefit from AI's improved performances and knowledge.AI, HCAI, and SAI systems are therefore specializations of each other (Fig. 3).",
    "For example, let's consider a simple AI system for cell classification.",
    "Physicians may require a better understanding of its decision-making process, asking for explanations, different ways of providing outputs, etc.",
    "Thus, the AI system can be specialized into an HCAI system by using HCI methods, which involve users in the system design and evaluation.",
    "Finally, the HCAI system can be further specialized into an SAI system by adopting ways of improving the system and the human knowledge incrementally and interactively through Human-AI collaboration."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}